service.name: Low Income Family Supplement
service.description: Low Income Family Supplement is an administrative name for the Low Income Supplement. The name applies to customers who received or were eligible for Family Tax Benefit (FTB) for 39 weeks or more in the previous financial year. It is an annual lump sum payment available to independent adults in low income households that do not receive adequate assistance through tax cuts or other assistance payments.
